cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

The paper deals with designing efficient convolutional neural architectures for different types of hardware, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper proposes a novel approach for Neural Architecture Search (NAS) that takes into account hardware diversity, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural engineering (cs.NE) fields. The paper also uses a coordinate ascent framework for the search, which is a technique commonly used in computer architecture (cs.AR) research.
